  "body": "Hi there,\r\nPuppeth do not deploy module explorer properly\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth 1.9.9 stable`\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nContext: Puppeth\r\nVia remote call I should be able to auto-deploy module explorer through steps:\r\n4. Manage network components -> (n) deploy new network component \r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nInitialzation passes, but \r\n`502 Bad Gateway\r\nnginx/1.17.6`\r\noccurs on reverse proxy side.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nDeploy new module explorer on private network\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution:\r\nadd env `POSTGRES_HOST_AUTH_METHOD=trust`\r\n`POSTGRES_HOST_AUTH_METHOD=trust /usr/local/bin/docker-entrypoint.sh postgres &' >> explorer.sh && \\` in `module_explorer.go`\r\n\r\n### Backtrace\r\nPostgres dies, because no password on admin is not preferred option. Either inject password or env `POSTGRES_HOST_AUTH_METHOD` ",
